unittitle.value: Records of the Faculty of Arts and Science

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: The collection contains deparment files created by the Faculty of Arts and Science dating from 1968 to 1986.

p.value: Published citations should take the following form: Identification of item, date (if known); The Records of the Faculty of Arts and Science; RG 21.0; box number; folder number; New York University Archives, New York University Libraries.
Founded in 1832, the CAS formed the foundation of the University. GSAS was added in 1886, awarding the second earned doctorate in the United States.
This collection contains departmental files of the Dean's office of the Faculty of Arts and Science.
